+# ImageMagick CVEs in Containers – Analysis & Justification
+
+## Overview
+
+This document provides analysis of ImageMagick CVEs reported by security scanners and explains why certain vulnerabilities are **not applicable** for Debian Bookworm (ImageMagick 6.x).
+
+---
+
+## ⚠️ CVE-2026-28493 – Not Applicable (ImageMagick 6.x)
+
+### Summary
+
+* **Type:** Out-of-bounds write
+* **Component:** SIXEL image decoder (`coders/sixel.c`)
+* **Root Cause:** Integer overflow due to `(int)` typecast
+* **Affected Branch:** ImageMagick 7.x only
+* **Debian Impact:** ❌ Not applicable
+
+---
+
+## Overview of the Vulnerability
+
+CVE-2026-28493 is caused by unsafe casting in the SIXEL decoder:
+
+```c id="sixelvuln"
+imbuf[(int) offset + x] = (sixel_pixel_t) color_index;
+```
+
+### Problem
+
+* `offset` may exceed `INT_MAX`
+* Casting to `(int)` truncates the value
+* Leads to **out-of-bounds memory writes**
+
+---
+
+## Why Debian Bookworm Is NOT Affected
+
+ImageMagick 6.9.11-60 (Debian Bookworm) uses a **different implementation**:
+
+### Key Differences
+
+1. **No `(int)` typecast**
+
+   * Uses `offset` directly
+
+2. **Safer data type**
+
+   * `offset` is `ssize_t` (64-bit)
+
+3. **Different write approach**
+
+   * Uses `memset()` for repeated writes
+   * Avoids unsafe loop indexing
+
+4. **Built-in bounds checks**
+
+   * Ensures writes stay within buffer limits
+
+---
+
+## Code Comparison
+
+### ImageMagick 7 (Vulnerable)
+
+```c id="sixel7"
+for (x = 0; x < repeat_count; x++)
+    imbuf[(int) offset + x] = (sixel_pixel_t) color_index;
+```
+
+### ImageMagick 6 (Debian Bookworm – Safe)
+
+```c id="sixel6"
+// Single pixel write
+imbuf[offset] = color_index;
+
+// Repeated write
+memset(imbuf + offset, color_index, repeat_count);
+```
+
+---
+
+## Verification
+
+| Check                    | Result                |
+| ------------------------ | --------------------- |
+| `(int)` cast on `offset` | ❌ Not present         |
+| `offset` type            | ✅ `ssize_t` (64-bit)  |
+| Buffer access pattern    | ✅ Direct + `memset()` |
+| Bounds validation        | ✅ Present             |
+
+---
+
+## Affected Versions
+
+| Version                                 | Status           |
+| --------------------------------------- | ---------------- |
+| ImageMagick 7.x (< 7.1.2-13)            | ❌ Vulnerable     |
+| ImageMagick 6.9.11-60 (Debian Bookworm) | ✅ Not vulnerable |
+| ImageMagick 6.x (all releases)          | ✅ Not vulnerable |
+
+---
+
+## Conclusion
+
+* Vulnerability exists only in **ImageMagick 7**
+* Debian Bookworm uses **ImageMagick 6**
+* Unsafe `(int)` cast is **absent**
+* Implementation is **safe by design**
+
+### ✅ Final Verdict
+
+**CVE-2026-28493 is NOT applicable to Debian Bookworm containers.**
+No patching or mitigation is required.
+
+---
+
+## Recommendation
+
+* Mark as **not applicable** in security reports
+* Do NOT attempt patching or backporting
+* Avoid unnecessary rebuilds
+
+---
+
+## References
+
+* Fix Commit (v7): https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick/commit/6cefe972445185cbb9c76651231d52512e0ec14b
+* Advisory: GHSA-r39q-jr8h-gcq2
+* Debian Tracker: https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-28493
+
+---
