+## ⚠️ CVE-2026-30929 – False Positive (ImageMagick 6.x)
+
+### Summary
+
+* **Type:** Stack-based buffer overflow
+* **Component:** `MagnifyImage` (resize implementation)
+* **Severity:** High (CVSS ~7.7–7.8)
+* **Affected Branch:** ImageMagick 7.x only
+* **Debian Impact:** ❌ Not applicable
+
+---
+
+## Overview of the Vulnerability
+
+CVE-2026-30929 affects the `MagnifyImage` function in ImageMagick.
+
+* Issue: Use of a fixed-size stack buffer
+* Risk: Buffer overflow when processing large images
+* Result: Stack corruption (CWE-121, CWE-787)
+
+---
+
+## Why Debian Bookworm Is NOT Affected
+
+### 1. Different Codebases (IM6 vs IM7)
+
+ImageMagick has two separate implementations:
+
+* **ImageMagick 6.x (Debian Bookworm)** → `magick/resize.c`
+* **ImageMagick 7.x (Affected)** → `MagickCore/resize.c`
+
+The vulnerability exists only in the **ImageMagick 7 implementation**.
+
+---
+
+### 2. Vulnerable Pattern Exists Only in IM7
+
+```c id="im7pattern"
+Quantum r[128];   // fixed-size stack buffer
+```
+
+* Fixed buffer size
+* Can overflow under certain conditions
+
+---
+
+### 3. ImageMagick 6 Uses a Safe Design
+
+```c id="im6pattern"
+PixelPacket *q;
+PixelPacket *r;
+
+r = q;   // pointer to allocated cache buffer
+```
+
+### Key Differences
+
+* No fixed-size stack buffer
+* Uses dynamically allocated memory
+* Writes performed via pointer arithmetic
+* Memory sized according to image dimensions
+
+---
+
+### 4. Safe Stack Usage in IM6
+
+```c id="im6safe"
+MagickRealType intensity[9];
+```
+
+* Small fixed array
+* Used in bounded loop (`i < 9`)
+* No overflow risk
+
+---
+
+### 5. Verification Evidence
+
+| Check                       | Result |
+| --------------------------- | ------ |
+| `Quantum r[128]` present    | ❌ No   |
+| Fixed-size stack buffer     | ❌ No   |
+| Pointer-based memory writes | ✅ Yes  |
+| Cache-backed allocation     | ✅ Yes  |
+
+---
+
+### 6. Why Scanners Flag It Incorrectly
+
+* CVE metadata groups IM6 and IM7 together
+* Version range includes `< 6.9.13-41`
+* Scanners rely on:
+
+  * Package name
+  * Version matching
+* They do **not inspect actual code implementation**
+
+---
+
+## Comparison
+
+| Aspect        | ImageMagick 7.x (Vulnerable) | ImageMagick 6.x (Debian Bookworm) |
+| ------------- | ---------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
+| File          | `MagickCore/resize.c`        | `magick/resize.c`                 |
+| Buffer        | `Quantum r[128]`             | `PixelPacket *r`                  |
+| Allocation    | Stack                        | Cache/heap                        |
+| Overflow risk | Yes                          | No                                |
+
+---
+
+## Conclusion
+
+* Vulnerability exists only in **ImageMagick 7**
+* Debian Bookworm uses **ImageMagick 6**
+* Vulnerable pattern is **absent**
+* Implementation is **safe by design**
+
+### ✅ Final Verdict
+
+**CVE-2026-30929 is a false positive for Debian Bookworm containers.**
+No patching or remediation is required.
+
+---
+
+## Recommendation
+
+* Mark as **false positive** in security reports
+* Do NOT attempt patching or backporting
+* Avoid unnecessary container rebuilds
+
